&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Position:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bluefish is seeking an experienced and client-centric Director of Professional Services to lead and scale our delivery pods. This role is a critical leader within the Strategy &amp;amp; Services organization, responsible for managing and developing Customer AI Strategists, AI Consultants, and Customer AI Analysts, and driving portfolio-level strategy, client retention, and renewal ownership across key industry verticals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Director of Professional Services, you&#39;ll play a central role in shaping how our organization delivers measurable AI marketing outcomes for the world&#39;s largest brands. You&#39;ll develop a portfolio and vertical point of view, build team processes in partnership with the Head of Professional Services, and serve as an accountable, senior voice in client relationships — ensuring that every engagement translates into strategic value and long-term partnership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Be Doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, coach, and manage a pod of Customer AI Strategists, AI Consultants, and AI Analysts aligned to specific industry verticals, driving high performance and career growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with the Head of Professional Services to build team processes, operating rhythms, and delivery frameworks that scale across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own portfolio-level strategy across multiple verticals within the same sector, developing a sharp vertical POV and ensuring consistency of outcomes across accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take ownership of portfolio renewals — proactively identifying risks, building the case for expansion, and leading renewal conversations with clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Frame client problems, make tradeoff calls, and be accountable for outcomes at the vertical level, bringing a strategic perspective to every client engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead cross-functional and client-facing conversations at senior levels (VP, SVP+), partnering with Product, Marketing, and Account Leads to drive alignment and shared accountability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with AI Strategists to develop vertical-specific narratives and views that inform client strategy and internal thinking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and scale best practices for client orchestration, workstream ownership, account planning, and performance measurement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to hiring, onboarding, and team design as the Professional Services organization continues to grow.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;12+ years of experience in client services, management consulting, enterprise customer success, or a related field, with meaningful experience managing senior client relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of owning portfolio-level outcomes — including renewals, expansions, and executive-level client engagement — across complex, multi-brand or multi-market accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong strategic thinking skills with the ability to frame ambiguous problems, make clear tradeoff decisions, and drive accountability across a team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading and developing high-performing delivery teams, with a coaching orientation and a focus on career growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communicator and executive presence — comfortable leading conversations with VP and SVP-level client stakeholders and cross-functional partners alike.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytically grounded, with experience working alongside data and strategy teams to develop insight-driven narratives and client recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Startup-ready attitude and comfort operating in a fast-moving environment where priorities evolve quickly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About B

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bluefish is defining agentic marketing and how we show up in the world matters as much as what we build. As our&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Events Lead&lt;/strong&gt;, you will own the full events function: from our inaugural owned thought leadership event to sponsored industry moments, client roundtables, and field experiences. You&#39;ll be both the strategist and the operator — the person who sees the big picture and makes sure every detail lands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a senior, high-ownership role for someone who knows how to build an events program from the ground up and isn&#39;t afraid to roll up their sleeves to do it.&lt;/p&gt;
